The Offer

Currently valued at USD $18 million with $5 million in investment and government grants, Dovetail Electric Aviation is raising a seed round (10% of company) to accelerate its go-to-market strategy and begin generating revenue within 3 years. Now is the time to get in on the ground floor of a company projected to be the next fixed-wing aircraft OEM with a USD $4B+ valuation. Wholesale and pre-approved investors can invest from a minimum of $5,000 AUD.

Important

The Offer for shares in Dovetail Electric Aviation is $3,600 USD per ordinary share, at a minimum investment of $5,000 AUD.

Any investment made in Dovetail will be made via a VentureCrowd trust, with VentureCrowd Nominees as Trustee. This allows investors to invest in $AUD, with the currency conversion being done by the Trust at the time of investment into the Company. Any variances between amounts invested into the Trust and by the Trust into the company will be handled by our Funds Management team upon the close of the deal. Please ensure to have your bank account detail updated on your VentureCrowd portal for any refund once this deal is closed.

Use of Funds and Exit Strategy

The initial development phase for Dovetail is largely focused on research and development activities for Dovetail’s first electric propulsion system. Dovetail is committed to bringing a product to market as quickly as possible, to fulfil the committed orders placed (a total of 69 conversions) at a value of $219 million dollars.

Activities within the development phase include bringing Dovetail’s initial battery-powered electric propulsion system to market (customised for a Cessna Caravan aircraft), including completing a first flight, numerous testing activities to validate the electric propulsion system, as well as certifying the product in Australia.

componentInstanceProperties.value:
What is Dovetail Electric Aviation?

Dovetail’s vision is to lead the regional and general aviation industry into an exciting new, sustainable era by enabling aviation operators to fly commercially viable regional routes in nil-emission, electric-powered aircraft. Dovetail is integrating innovative electric power plant technology onto legacy aircraft to enable environmentally friendly and financially viable travel.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Problem and Market

Australia relies heavily on air transport to connect remote and regional communities. The Australian government supports regional travel due to the distances involved and with road access to many communities often cut for several months during the wet season, in particular areas regular air services offer the only reliable means of transport.

Australia has the fourth largest fleet of Cessna Caravans in the world, Dovetail’s initial aircraft target to retrofit. Offering a cost-efficient innovation that adds value to an aircraft, rather than forcing an operator to purchase a brand-new (expensive) aircraft, this approach enables a circular economy, providing operators with the ability to upgrade their combustion motor at the end of its life for one-fifth of the cost.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Dovetail Electric Aviation Solution

Dovetail’s Electric Propulsion System reduces aviation operators’ operating costs by 40% and increases a motor life by three times the current standard. NASA published a study, noting that if regional aircraft operating costs reduce by 40%, market demand increases by a factor of 10. This will revolutionise regional transport, increasing the market significantly.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Competitive Advantage

Dovetail is getting to market as quickly as possible. The company is applying for a Supplemental Type Certificate (STC) (for retrofitting an aircraft) is the quickest way to market. It saves time and money by modifying the current aircraft to replace its motor. The value add is that the business utilises existing aircraft assets rather than forcing fleet renewal upon aircraft operators, especially given the impact COVID has had on the aviation industry. This accelerates uptake, and keeps asset ownership high by adding value to current assets. The small commuter aircraft market is our target. First, because small aircraft STCs are faster and easier to approve. But just as important or even more so, is because we are bringing to this segment a revolution and renaissance at the same time, with demand x 10 when electrification reduces operating costs by 40%.

We focus on a full electric conversion, not hybrid (internal combustion engine, more complex and less cost effective), and we will be the first ones to certify a nil emissions Cessna Caravan. Unlike competitors in the market, we believe nil emissions is the way forward. Battery-power will enable us to be first to market, but long-term, hydrogen will outperform battery technology (as it significantly outperforms in terms of range). Currently, the standards for hydrogen are yet to be identified by the aviation regulatory bodies. Instead, some preliminary standards for batteries have been published and identified, with aviation precedents in the market.

Dovetail Electric Aviation’s team are Subject Matter Experts in the industry already with decades of experience in aviation and electric aviation. Dovetail has advanced concepts for adding battery packs to our airframe, relying on modules developed by specialised companies (they will obtain Type Certificates for them) but optimised for airframe integration by us, what will be key elements of our STC and as such, proprietary IP. We are doing the same with fuel cells, with a clear objective to develop efficient systems, because above all we are systems integrators.

Fees

Investors invest through a VentureCrowd Trust, which VentureCrowd manages as a single asset. We charge an annual management fee to investors, payable on exit and we only charge a performance fee where an exit delivers profit, thereby aligning ourselves with investor outcomes.

  • Contribution Fee: 1.1% This is the fee charged by the Trustee for establishing the Trust and the purchasing entity, structuring the overall investment and raising capital by issuing Units. Payable upon acceptance of your investment by the Trustee.
  • Management Fee: 1.65% per annum (charged on conversion or exit).
  • Performance Fee: 20% of the profit. We only charge a performance fee on conversion or exit.

Risks

Investing in private companies is risky. Issuers using this facility include new or rapidly growing ventures. Investment in these types of ventures is speculative and carries high risks. You may lose your entire investment, and you should be in a position to bear this risk without undue hardship. Even if the company is successful, the value of your investment and any return on the investment could be reduced if the company issues more shares. Your investment is unlikely to be liquid. This means you are unlikely to be able to sell your shares quickly or at all if you need the money or decide that this investment is not right for you. Even though you have remedies for misleading statements in the offer document or misconduct by the company, you may have difficulty recovering your money. There are rules for handling your money. However, if your money is handled inappropriately or the person operating this platform becomes insolvent, you may have difficulty recovering your money. Ask questions, read all information given carefully, and seek independent financial advice before committing yourself to any investment.
